01:32.887 --> 01:35.261
[phone ringing]

01:37.720 --> 01:40.804
-[Marie] Mom, the phone.
-[Cathy] I'll get it upstairs.

01:40.804 --> 01:43.136
[Marie] Pop,
is Grandma all right?

01:43.136 --> 01:45.637
[Richy] Yeah. Just a little
upset today, that's all.

01:56.428 --> 01:59.970
-Hello.
-[Hayes] Cathy?

01:59.970 --> 02:02.345
The fuckin' balls on you,
Tommy.

02:02.345 --> 02:05.512
-I'm sorry. I'm sorry, Cathy.
-  You're sorry?

02:05.512 --> 02:08.178
You're sorry? Everything
my fuckin' husband did for you.

02:08.178 --> 02:10.261
You're family.
You're gonna call here?

02:10.261 --> 02:12.929
You rat fuck piece of shit!

02:12.929 --> 02:15.929
Frankie's shitty little brother
Jimmy was the rat.

02:15.929 --> 02:18.261
Tell me you think I'm wrong.

02:23.804 --> 02:25.220
-[Hayes] Cathy?
-[banging]

02:25.220 --> 02:27.178
Cathy!

02:29.136 --> 02:30.845
-[phone clatters]
-Fuck you!

02:30.845 --> 02:33.428
-Cathy, listen to me.
-[dial tone]

02:33.428 --> 02:37.887
[sighs]
Fuck!

02:37.887 --> 02:40.762
[bagpipes playing
"Amazing Grace"]

02:44.720 --> 02:47.804
[bagpipes continue]

03:12.762 --> 03:14.220
[car approaches]

03:16.595 --> 03:18.637
[tires skid]

03:34.428 --> 03:36.553
-Shit.
-[phone rings]

03:37.970 --> 03:39.553
The fuck do you want?

03:39.553 --> 03:41.970
[man] We have a location
on Tommy Hayes.

03:41.970 --> 03:43.387
Well, bring him home.

04:06.595 --> 04:08.220
[newscaster]
It's a beautiful weekend

04:08.220 --> 04:09.929
here in Western New York.

04:09.929 --> 04:12.387
Lots and lots of fun activities
for the family.

04:12.387 --> 04:14.136
Check out
the Allentown Arts Festival.

04:14.136 --> 04:15.595
And don't forget...

04:15.595 --> 04:18.095
-[all shouting]
-Don't move, don't move!

04:18.095 --> 04:21.804
[agent] Thomas Hayes!
You are under arrest!

04:21.804 --> 04:23.637
[Tommy groaning]

04:25.011 --> 04:26.679
Fuck you!

04:26.679 --> 04:28.053
Fuck!

04:29.637 --> 04:31.679
[indistinct chatter]

04:31.679 --> 04:35.970
[Irish music plays]

04:51.303 --> 04:54.804
[indistinct chatter]

04:54.804 --> 04:56.303
Hey, excuse me.
Excuse me.

05:08.512 --> 05:09.929
[Jackie] Hey,

05:09.929 --> 05:12.512
they found this
with Hank's shit.

05:12.512 --> 05:14.178
How'd you get
his belongings?

05:14.178 --> 05:16.679
I imagine
he meant that for you.

05:22.220 --> 05:26.679
You warned me.
I forgot. Lincoln Steffens:

05:26.679 --> 05:31.720
"Boston has brought corruption
to the level of an art form."

05:31.720 --> 05:33.345
I guess gettin' fucked is--

05:33.345 --> 05:36.804
is what I get
for trusting another person.

05:38.679 --> 05:41.053
So, here we are, huh?

05:41.053 --> 05:46.261
You made the bust, the Ryans
are the Feds' problem now.

05:46.261 --> 05:48.762
I'll take care of ya.

05:48.762 --> 05:51.053
Nah. Don't.

05:51.053 --> 05:54.136
"As usual, I alone was wrong.

05:54.136 --> 05:56.804
All wrong....

05:56.804 --> 05:58.345
but all right, too."

05:58.345 --> 06:01.970
Again. Steffens.

06:06.220 --> 06:09.053
Ya know,
when I was a kid,

06:09.053 --> 06:11.261
we were fuckin' poor.

06:11.261 --> 06:13.887
You could tell, 'cause of
the advent of redlining,

06:13.887 --> 06:16.220
we liv-- lived
with the black people.

06:16.220 --> 06:19.970
And I used to sneak
into the Baptist Church

06:19.970 --> 06:22.303
because I loved to...

06:22.303 --> 06:25.178
I just loved
to listen to 'em sing.

06:25.178 --> 06:28.512
I mean, I would-- I would
sit in the back of the church

06:28.512 --> 06:31.512
and I would see these people
sing and testify,

06:31.512 --> 06:34.136
and I would think to myself,

06:34.136 --> 06:38.178
what do they have
that I don't?

06:38.178 --> 06:42.929
What do they know
that I don't know...

06:42.929 --> 06:46.762
that lets 'em smile...
and sing like that?

06:49.303 --> 06:51.804
I never figured it out.

06:51.804 --> 06:53.261
Never.

06:55.220 --> 06:58.595
All I'm sayin' is, Dee...

06:58.595 --> 07:00.428
you're not alone.

07:03.804 --> 07:06.428
When did you stop
giving a shit?

07:09.470 --> 07:11.970
Honestly...

07:11.970 --> 07:13.929
I couldn't tell ya.

07:18.261 --> 07:21.303
♪ melancholy music plays ♪

07:30.136 --> 07:32.261
[indistinct chatter]

07:34.011 --> 07:35.553
Why are you talking to him?

07:35.553 --> 07:37.303
Signa is dead
because he had to be

07:37.303 --> 07:40.345
the great fuckin' Jackie Rohr.

07:40.345 --> 07:43.929
You think he's the only person
who knows how to play people?

07:43.929 --> 07:46.637
Believe me,
I didn't forget what you said.

07:46.637 --> 07:48.637
And when I come for him,

07:48.637 --> 07:52.387
he ain't gonna
see me comin'.

07:52.387 --> 07:53.637
[Barrett]
The state cop was killed

07:53.637 --> 07:55.637
during the commission
of a federal crime.

07:55.637 --> 07:57.470
[Jackie]
You know, as a U.S. Attorney,

07:57.470 --> 07:59.804
you are a living,
breathing cliché.

07:59.804 --> 08:02.762
You are doin' exactly what
we mocked the nuns for doin'

08:02.762 --> 08:04.595
back at school
when we got in trouble--

08:04.595 --> 08:06.595
you're makin' a federal case
outta nothin'.

08:06.595 --> 08:09.095
Just kick the Ryan brothers
down to Suffolk

08:09.095 --> 08:11.720
and let the D.A. try them
for the triple murder in Revere.

08:11.720 --> 08:15.178
Of course, you don't care
about the Ryan brothers.

08:15.178 --> 08:17.553
You already got your episode
of Chronicle  on Channel 5.

08:17.553 --> 08:19.804
And don't think I don't know
you're gonna be throwing

08:19.804 --> 08:21.178
that one in my face in my face
for the next ten years

08:21.178 --> 08:23.011
like you did the Angiulo bust.

08:23.011 --> 08:25.637
I know I'm real tired
of hearing about Jerry Angiulo.

08:25.637 --> 08:28.011
-Just sayin'.
-[Jackie] Not for nothin'.

08:28.011 --> 08:30.011
But the Feds don't have
the greatest reputation

08:30.011 --> 08:31.553
in this town right now,

08:31.553 --> 08:33.512
and the papers are startin'
to get smart.

08:33.512 --> 08:35.637
Don't look too good
for you, either.

08:35.637 --> 08:38.220
And yet here
we are again on Chronicle,

08:38.220 --> 08:40.595
and once again
people are hearin' "FBI"

08:40.595 --> 08:43.970
and they think
of Efrem Zimbalist, Jr.

08:43.970 --> 08:46.220
And why is that?

08:46.220 --> 08:48.553
Because of me.

08:54.345 --> 08:55.970
What do you want me to do?

08:55.970 --> 08:58.553
This kid Ward, his case
doesn't mean anything to you,

08:58.553 --> 09:01.053
but to him,
a win would mean something.

09:01.053 --> 09:03.303
Hank Signa was like a father
to this kid.

09:03.303 --> 09:04.720
Got shot right
in front of him.

09:04.720 --> 09:06.345
Come on,
give him a break!

09:08.637 --> 09:11.637
Uh...

09:11.637 --> 09:13.804
if you want to ask us
as a favor.

09:15.512 --> 09:17.303
You cheap, miserable fuck.

09:17.303 --> 09:20.387
Ward used to work for you.

09:23.053 --> 09:24.595
All right.

09:24.595 --> 09:26.970
As a favor, then.

09:26.970 --> 09:29.178
I owe you.

09:29.178 --> 09:31.845
Then what the fuck

09:31.845 --> 09:33.845
is this Ryan brothers case
doing on my desk?

09:33.845 --> 09:35.679
I don't need this shit
right now. Get rid of it.

09:36.595 --> 09:37.845
[Jimmy] Just listen. Listen.

09:37.845 --> 09:39.261
[stammering]
You fuckin'--

09:39.261 --> 09:40.970
You keep sayin'
the same thing...

09:40.970 --> 09:42.720
over and over
and over again. Okay?

09:42.720 --> 09:44.679
So I'm gonna keep tellin' you
the same thing back.

09:44.679 --> 09:47.637
Immunity.
I want blanket fuckin' immunity.

09:47.637 --> 09:50.178
You expect immunity
for everything,

09:50.178 --> 09:51.595
everything you've ever done?

09:51.595 --> 09:53.762
You think I'm gonna get up
on the fuckin' stand,

09:53.762 --> 09:54.929
talk about
all the shit I've done

09:54.929 --> 09:56.470
just so you can
fuck me later?

09:56.470 --> 09:58.303
I hate to derail
your train of thought here,

09:58.303 --> 10:00.970
but are you
out of your mind?

10:00.970 --> 10:02.929
You don't exactly have the best
pharmaceutical facilities,

10:02.929 --> 10:05.303
this place,
and it's been about 24 hours

10:05.303 --> 10:07.595
since I had the medication
that I need.

10:07.595 --> 10:09.345
So you're not too far
off the mark.

10:09.345 --> 10:11.345
You wanna take a little trip
down to Bridgewood, hmm?

10:11.345 --> 10:13.512
A little 72-hour
observation?

10:13.512 --> 10:15.303
Yeah, withhold medical care,
that's good.

10:15.303 --> 10:17.303
Hell, I might even leave here
with a civil suit.

10:17.303 --> 10:18.804
I guess that's what
I should have expected

10:18.804 --> 10:20.929
of an affirmative action hire.

10:20.929 --> 10:23.970
[Rachel] Why is he
puttin' up with this shit?

10:23.970 --> 10:25.762
You remember
the best lay of your life?

10:25.762 --> 10:28.720
How is that question
at all pertinent?

10:28.720 --> 10:32.470
I remember mine.
Girl I knew in law school.

10:32.470 --> 10:35.261
Susie. She had a body
like Jane Russell.

10:35.261 --> 10:36.804
Kind of a goofy face, but...

10:36.804 --> 10:38.679
Then I met Elizabeth.

10:38.679 --> 10:41.220
Very pretty, thought she'd
look good on a campaign poster,

10:41.220 --> 10:43.845
so I married the face.

10:43.845 --> 10:46.970
Being a prosecutor
just isn't enough for Dee Ward.

10:46.970 --> 10:49.762
He-- He just won't take
the collar on Fall River,

10:49.762 --> 10:52.011
he wants to solve Revere too,

10:52.011 --> 10:54.261
and make himself
a nice campaign poster.

10:54.261 --> 10:57.303
I don't know.
Maybe he's smart.

10:57.303 --> 11:00.053
Or maybe he'll end up like me,

11:00.053 --> 11:03.303
wondering why he just couldn't
leave well enough alone.

11:03.303 --> 11:05.804
[chair scraping]

11:05.804 --> 11:07.804
-Okay.
-Okay.

11:10.261 --> 11:12.345
I'll be honest with you.

11:12.345 --> 11:15.804
I'll put you guys away
for killin' my friend

11:15.804 --> 11:18.970
for attempted robbery,
etcetera, etcetera.

11:18.970 --> 11:22.887
But I won't rest easy not having
justice for those guards.

11:22.887 --> 11:25.720
[laughs]

11:25.720 --> 11:28.720
Oh. Is that what
all this shit's about?

11:28.720 --> 11:31.637
-Is it really fuckin' justice?
-Yeah, really. Justice.

11:31.637 --> 11:35.720
So... I'm gonna put you
in the County tank.

11:35.720 --> 11:39.637
I'm gonna put Thomas Hayes
in the same tank.

11:39.637 --> 11:41.553
Then I'm gonna tell
the screws up there

11:41.553 --> 11:43.470
-that one of you killed a cop...
-Yeah?

11:43.470 --> 11:45.553
...and the other is a rat.

11:45.553 --> 11:48.679
See if you can bullshit
your way out of that.

11:48.679 --> 11:52.512
[laughing]
Yeah. Yeah.

11:52.512 --> 11:55.136
-Well, you're new to this.
-Hmm?

11:55.136 --> 11:57.428
Not the job. Maybe I was
a little out of line

11:57.428 --> 11:58.595
with that
affirmative action thing,

11:58.595 --> 12:01.637
but you're new
to this  situation.

12:01.637 --> 12:06.220
Which is a situation
where you're fucked.

12:06.220 --> 12:09.470
You're in trouble.

12:09.470 --> 12:11.762
-Me? I'm in trouble?
-Yeah. Yeah.

12:11.762 --> 12:14.053
See, me, I been in trouble
my whole life.

12:14.053 --> 12:16.345
I couldn't possibly
make this worse for myself,

12:16.345 --> 12:18.553
but I got nothin' to lose.

12:18.553 --> 12:22.095
Which means, like it or not,

12:22.095 --> 12:24.136
you're even more fucked.

12:24.136 --> 12:27.303
You've been working this Revere
robbery for-- for four months,

12:27.303 --> 12:29.095
and now you're gonna put me
and my brother

12:29.095 --> 12:32.470
and all my friends away for this
bullshit down in Fall River.

12:32.470 --> 12:36.095
But that won't solve
who killed those Revere guards.

12:39.178 --> 12:41.845
I can do that for ya, though.

12:44.387 --> 12:46.387
For immunity.

12:46.387 --> 12:50.637
I'll say it again:
blanket immunity.

12:54.804 --> 12:56.970
[gate lock buzzes]

13:07.345 --> 13:09.261
Heard you talked to Ward.

13:09.261 --> 13:11.136
Yeah, I got myself
a little heat.

13:11.136 --> 13:12.637
What'd you tell him?

13:12.637 --> 13:14.595
I didn't say anything
about you.

13:14.595 --> 13:16.303
Jesus fuckin' Christ,
you're the only person I know

13:16.303 --> 13:17.970
that talks more than I do.

13:17.970 --> 13:19.929
You worry about me
runnin' my  fuckin' mouth?

13:22.720 --> 13:26.011
You know,
I went to that funeral.

13:26.011 --> 13:28.845
That state trooper that
your shithead friend killed.

13:28.845 --> 13:31.845
I like to watch the crowds
at funerals. You know?

13:31.845 --> 13:33.970
You can always tell when
the son of a bitch wasn't liked,

13:33.970 --> 13:35.845
but this guy,
people were genuine.

13:35.845 --> 13:37.804
And it got me thinkin'.

13:37.804 --> 13:40.637
Have you ever thought about what
your funeral's gonna look like?

13:40.637 --> 13:42.303
Do you know how many
fuckin' times

13:42.303 --> 13:44.011
I've had my life
threatened today?

13:44.011 --> 13:45.804
No, I'm not talkin'
about that.

13:45.804 --> 13:48.345
I'm-- I'm just sayin',
do you think that anyone

13:48.345 --> 13:51.637
is gonna feel anything
other then relief when you die?

13:51.637 --> 13:53.261
Your parents or your brother

13:53.261 --> 13:56.762
or, uh, that girl whose life
you ruined down in Florida?

13:56.762 --> 13:59.136
I mean, I'm sincerely
not tryin' to be a prick here.

13:59.136 --> 14:03.470
You and me both, there is
gonna be people at our funerals

14:03.470 --> 14:06.387
who are finally gonna be able
to fuckin' breathe.

14:06.387 --> 14:08.053
You see what I'm sayin'?

14:08.053 --> 14:10.762
And you're the guy
that I can talk to about this

14:10.762 --> 14:12.387
who will understand,
who's sittin' in this cell

14:12.387 --> 14:14.095
for rattin' on his brother
and his friends.

14:14.095 --> 14:17.136
What-- What you tryin'
to get at here?

14:17.136 --> 14:20.553
I think the Catholic guilt
has finally gotten to me.

14:20.553 --> 14:22.887
I've hurt a lot of people,

14:22.887 --> 14:26.220
and I would like to be able
to bring them some relief.

14:29.762 --> 14:32.303
Meanin' if I talk,
then I'm dead.

14:32.303 --> 14:34.553
You know, I almost fuckin'
believed for a second,

14:34.553 --> 14:36.887
for a second, that you're
a decent human being.

14:39.345 --> 14:42.970
Ya know,
I know a lot, Jackie.

14:42.970 --> 14:44.887
-Oh, you do, huh?
-Yeah. I read the papers.

14:44.887 --> 14:46.929
All those stories in the Globe,
they just won't go away--

14:46.929 --> 14:49.136
the Bulger brothers
and the FBI.

14:49.136 --> 14:52.261
-Fuck do you know about that?
-Well, I could tell someone

14:52.261 --> 14:55.220
how the relationship between
the FBI and an informant works,

14:55.220 --> 14:57.303
among some other things,
like how the FBI

14:57.303 --> 14:59.053
looks the other way,
you drop a body.

14:59.053 --> 15:00.470
Like I said, Jackie,
I know a lot of things.

15:00.470 --> 15:02.428
Seems you do.

15:02.428 --> 15:06.428
Which shows you the difference
between wisdom and intelligence,

15:06.428 --> 15:09.011
because if you were wiser,
you would keep that to yourself

15:09.011 --> 15:10.720
and let everyone think
that you were smart.

15:10.720 --> 15:12.345
Yeah, but see,
I-I get nervous,

15:12.345 --> 15:14.970
I just start talkin', ya know?
I always been that way.

15:14.970 --> 15:20.053
Now, I would be a lot calmer
answering questions

15:20.053 --> 15:21.929
if I had blanket immunity.

15:21.929 --> 15:25.053
Now, if only there was
some decent fuckin' human being

15:25.053 --> 15:27.595
who could understand that
and who was wise enough

15:27.595 --> 15:29.720
to do me that favor.

15:31.136 --> 15:33.470
I like you, kid.

15:33.470 --> 15:34.929
I really do.

15:34.929 --> 15:37.095
I mean, I talk to you,
and I don't feel so alone

15:37.095 --> 15:39.095
bein' the biggest
piece of shit in the world.

15:40.637 --> 15:42.595
Yeah, the feeling's mutual.

15:43.970 --> 15:45.136
Faggot.

15:50.387 --> 15:51.136
"Faggot."

15:52.553 --> 15:54.428
Shoulda killed
that motherfucker.

15:57.178 --> 15:59.845
[rain pitter-pattering]

15:59.845 --> 16:03.303
♪ dramatic music playing ♪

16:14.845 --> 16:16.261
[Jenny]
I just don't understand.

16:16.261 --> 16:17.512
[Jackie] What did you think
was goin' on?

16:17.512 --> 16:18.887
[Jenny]
Did you think had

16:18.887 --> 16:22.095
some kind of an arrangement?
Like an agreement?

16:22.095 --> 16:23.762
Are you really gonna look me
in the eye, Jackie,

16:23.762 --> 16:27.178
and tell me you thought that
what you were doing was okay?

16:27.178 --> 16:28.929
I just don't understand how

16:28.929 --> 16:31.261
you could lie like that
that another person.

16:31.261 --> 16:34.929
I understand lying--
I understand lying to yourself.

16:34.929 --> 16:37.428
But how you ignore
that sense of empathy

16:37.428 --> 16:41.053
that just tells you "no."
I don't get that.

16:41.053 --> 16:44.303
Or maybe that's the part
of you that scares me the most.

16:44.303 --> 16:45.512
Jennifer--

16:45.512 --> 16:47.679
I tried being
with another man.

16:47.679 --> 16:50.595
Don't-- Don't say anything.
Listen to me. I tried.

16:50.595 --> 16:52.720
I-- I was there with him

16:52.720 --> 16:55.887
and I just kept
thinkin' about you.

16:55.887 --> 16:59.095
How it'd make you feel,
how it'd make me feel,

16:59.095 --> 17:01.178
and I felt-- I felt awful,
I felt sick to my stomach.

17:01.178 --> 17:04.553
All you were thinkin' about
then was yourself.

17:04.553 --> 17:06.720
Not me, Jennifer.
You. Yourself.

17:06.720 --> 17:09.136
Wanna know what
I really thought?

17:09.136 --> 17:11.553
I thought I didn't
feel anything for you.

17:13.845 --> 17:15.512
But I was wrong.

17:15.512 --> 17:18.178
And now I really
don't understand

17:18.178 --> 17:20.387
how you could be with
all those other women--

17:20.387 --> 17:22.929
unless you really didn't
feel anything for me at all.

17:22.929 --> 17:24.929
No, that's not true.
I do. I do.

17:24.929 --> 17:26.887
Okay, then how could you
come into our house,

17:26.887 --> 17:29.512
look me in the face,
and not feel awful?

17:30.637 --> 17:33.470
Look at me.

17:33.470 --> 17:36.303
Really look.

17:36.303 --> 17:39.261
Do I look like anything like
the guy that you married?

17:40.970 --> 17:43.387
Look at my face.
I mean, look hard.

17:43.387 --> 17:45.261
It shows.

17:46.929 --> 17:48.261
What shows?

17:50.095 --> 17:53.095
The sins. The loathing.

17:55.512 --> 17:59.428
Jackie, if you really
want us to work again...

17:59.428 --> 18:02.679
be that man
I always thought you were.

18:07.637 --> 18:09.095
I don't know.

18:10.762 --> 18:12.637
If you really
feel that way,

18:12.637 --> 18:14.929
maybe you should
just stay here.

18:32.595 --> 18:34.136
What is this shit?

18:34.136 --> 18:35.804
Didn't know
you still worked here.

18:35.804 --> 18:39.428
The guns. From Fall River?
The FBI selling them at auction?

18:39.428 --> 18:42.053
Are you kiddin'?
Are we fuckin' gun dealers now?

18:42.053 --> 18:44.303
What are you, afraid
they're going to Israel?

18:44.303 --> 18:46.095
Money funneled to the Contras?
What?

