conspiracy to commit

36:10.011 --> 36:12.428
armed bank robbery,
how do you find the defendant?

36:12.428 --> 36:14.053
[juror] Guilty.

36:14.053 --> 36:15.887
[clerk] On count four,
possession of illegal firearms.

36:15.887 --> 36:17.136
-[juror] Guilty.
-[clerk] On count five,

36:17.136 --> 36:18.512
trafficking
of illegal firearms...

36:18.512 --> 36:20.011
...on count six, carjacking...

36:20.011 --> 36:21.637
...how do you find
the defendant...

36:21.637 --> 36:23.637
[voices fade]

36:23.637 --> 36:25.637
♪ dramatic music plays ♪

36:28.011 --> 36:29.470
[handcuffs click]

36:42.929 --> 36:45.679
I can tell them, Ma.
I can talk to them.

36:45.679 --> 36:47.553
That's not how it works,
sweetheart.

36:47.553 --> 36:49.053
But I saw him, I saw him do it.

36:50.303 --> 36:53.053
You saw what?
What did you see?

36:53.053 --> 36:54.804
I saw Uncle Jimmy hit Kelly.

36:59.553 --> 37:01.345
I know you did, baby.

37:03.220 --> 37:05.220
Then why is Dad
going to jail?

37:05.220 --> 37:07.053
[sighs]

37:09.095 --> 37:12.929
-'Cause your father got caught.
-How?

37:12.929 --> 37:15.178
'Cause Uncle Jimmy
told the police on him.

37:15.178 --> 37:17.845
But Uncle Jimmy
killed somebody.

37:17.845 --> 37:21.387
Yeah, they know that.

37:21.387 --> 37:24.178
I'm gonna tell you somethin'.

37:24.178 --> 37:28.261
No one cares.

37:28.261 --> 37:30.553
The people that are in charge,
they got what they wanted,

37:30.553 --> 37:32.387
and that's all that matters,

37:32.387 --> 37:34.595
and they don't give a shit
about the rest.

37:34.595 --> 37:36.345
What about us?

37:40.095 --> 37:42.887
What'd your father always say?

37:42.887 --> 37:44.553
"I'll take care of it."

37:46.887 --> 37:48.053
Yeah.

37:51.220 --> 37:52.720
And now it's our turn
to do that.

37:54.053 --> 37:56.387
♪ dramatic music plays ♪

37:58.053 --> 37:59.387
[officer]
I don't know how you managed

37:59.387 --> 38:01.136
to pull this shit off,
ya bastard.

38:01.136 --> 38:02.804
You conned
a nigger prosecutor.

38:02.804 --> 38:04.428
[laughs] Yeah. Yeah.

38:04.428 --> 38:06.178
Why? You got any bodies
hanging over your head?

38:06.178 --> 38:07.804
Because I got the
get-out-of-jail-free card.

38:07.804 --> 38:08.762
I'll fuckin' cop to 'em for ya.

38:13.220 --> 38:16.387
[officer] Oh, you're
a fuckin' prince, Jimmy.

38:32.303 --> 38:34.679
[Jackie] Slide 'em in the trunk,
will ya, Bart?

38:34.679 --> 38:36.887
Oh!

38:36.887 --> 38:38.804
What's this?

38:38.804 --> 38:40.178
Did you finally
have that stroke?

38:40.178 --> 38:41.929
Do you even know what day it is?

38:41.929 --> 38:44.095
She won't let me
into my own home.

38:44.095 --> 38:47.553
-Who?
-Jennifer Marie.

38:47.553 --> 38:49.095
Your daughter?

38:49.095 --> 38:52.512
Your own daughter
threw you out on the street?

38:52.512 --> 38:54.595
What could you have possibly
have done to deserve

38:54.595 --> 38:56.845
that kind of treatment
from your own daughter?

38:56.845 --> 38:59.053
Enough bullshit.
I helped you!

38:59.053 --> 39:01.178
And do you know why
you were able to do that?

39:01.178 --> 39:03.679
Because no matter how
bad I treated that woman,

39:03.679 --> 39:05.512
there was nothing
I could do that was

39:05.512 --> 39:07.261
any worse than what you've done.

39:07.261 --> 39:11.470
And you think that now,
for the first time in her life,

39:11.470 --> 39:14.720
she stands on her hind legs
and I'm gonna knock her back?

39:14.720 --> 39:18.136
Nah.
I don't think so.

39:18.136 --> 39:20.762
You're just like everyone.

39:20.762 --> 39:25.303
You can't seem to learn
that you ain't that good...

39:25.303 --> 39:27.387
and I ain't that bad.

39:27.387 --> 39:29.220
I got nowhere to go!

39:34.387 --> 39:37.345
You know, ya look pretty good
for an old broad.

39:37.345 --> 39:40.261
Yeah. I mean, once ya...
once ya clean up.

39:40.261 --> 39:42.220
So, here's what we're gonna do.

39:42.220 --> 39:44.845
I'm gonna get you a corner on
the other side of the Common.

39:44.845 --> 39:46.637
You stand out there
for a few hours,

39:46.637 --> 39:50.470
and whatever money you make,
you give me 60%,

39:50.470 --> 39:53.095
and I will take real good
fuckin' care of ya.

39:53.095 --> 39:55.512
You fuckin' pig!

39:57.762 --> 39:59.929
-Thanks, Bart.
-Take care, Jackie.

40:11.053 --> 40:13.595
[phone rings]

40:25.178 --> 40:26.637
Hello?

40:26.637 --> 40:27.845
[Josh] Decourcy.

40:29.220 --> 40:31.303
Uh...

40:31.303 --> 40:34.178
Jos-- Josh, hey, you don't--
you don't have to say anything.

40:34.178 --> 40:36.178
I'm sorry.
You understand?

40:36.178 --> 40:38.136
-Y-Yeah.
-The way that trial went,

40:38.136 --> 40:40.011
I know the reality
of what happened,

40:40.011 --> 40:41.512
but your opposition
will destroy us

40:41.512 --> 40:43.470
for the deal you
cut with that man.

40:43.470 --> 40:46.470
Nah-- Hey, you don't-- you don't
have to explain, I get it.

40:46.470 --> 40:49.762
You-- You can't back a candidate
for City Council

40:49.762 --> 40:52.470
who just gave a killer immunity.

40:52.470 --> 40:53.970
Thanks for
making this easy on me.

40:53.970 --> 40:55.470
Yeah. Yeah.

40:58.303 --> 41:00.136
[disconnects]

41:05.011 --> 41:06.220
[Siobhan] Who was that?

41:07.553 --> 41:10.970
[Decourcy] My former
campaign manager.

41:10.970 --> 41:12.804
He calls now?

41:15.387 --> 41:17.512
Now?

41:17.512 --> 41:21.178
Are you really surprised
that Josh would take

41:21.178 --> 41:24.011
the opportunity
to fuck me in the ass?

41:24.011 --> 41:26.136
-Heh heh heh.
-[Siobhan sighs]

41:28.261 --> 41:31.762
I feel like such a fool.

41:35.011 --> 41:37.512
[sighs]
Things are bad now, but--

41:37.512 --> 41:39.303
-They'll only get worse.
-Baby...

41:39.303 --> 41:41.303
They gave me the rope,

41:41.303 --> 41:44.679
and I proved them all right.

41:44.679 --> 41:46.845
Everything they said about me,

41:46.845 --> 41:47.929
even the shit that wasn't true,

41:47.929 --> 41:51.011
I managed to prove them right.

41:51.011 --> 41:53.011
And there isn't
a single one of 'em

41:53.011 --> 41:55.970
who won't take the opportunity
to make sure that I know

41:55.970 --> 41:59.553
they didn't need to kill me,
I did the killing myself.

41:59.553 --> 42:02.470
You took a beating.

42:02.470 --> 42:05.053
What did you tell me
when I couldn't

42:05.053 --> 42:06.887
get an offer from
a single law firm?

42:09.011 --> 42:10.595
What did you tell me
when I cried?

42:10.595 --> 42:12.553
-Siobhan.
-What did you say to me?

42:12.553 --> 42:14.679
-Don't do this.
-What did you say?

42:14.679 --> 42:19.428
It's easier to bleed
than to sweat.

42:19.428 --> 42:22.929
-That's right.
-It's from an old Poitier movie.

42:22.929 --> 42:24.720
The line's still apt.

42:27.095 --> 42:30.261
Feel bad for yourself tonight.

42:30.261 --> 42:33.887
And get up tomorrow
and go back to work.

42:35.428 --> 42:38.095
I honestly don't think I can.

42:38.095 --> 42:41.387
You were proud enough
to take the risk,

42:41.387 --> 42:43.845
to put us in this position.

42:43.845 --> 42:46.095
Be proud enough
to accept the loss.

42:48.512 --> 42:53.428
Nah, [stammering] I just can't
take feeling this dirty!

42:53.428 --> 42:54.762
We've all been dirty.

42:54.762 --> 42:55.762
No, no.

42:57.595 --> 42:59.929
You know...

42:59.929 --> 43:03.595
I-I just need
to be honest with you.

43:03.595 --> 43:06.387
To feel like I can
stand to breathe,

43:06.387 --> 43:08.428
I need to be honest
with someone.

43:08.428 --> 43:11.261
And I fucked that up before...
and it--

43:11.261 --> 43:13.345
Nothing's fucked for good.

43:13.345 --> 43:17.053
Because I'm-- I'm here.

43:17.053 --> 43:19.970
I'm vulnerable here.

43:19.970 --> 43:23.136
And I-I can't take the idea
of you seeing me like this

43:23.136 --> 43:27.470
and-- and not trusting me
enough to do the same.

43:29.136 --> 43:30.804
I love you.

43:33.887 --> 43:35.804
You trust me?

43:36.970 --> 43:38.970
I couldn't love you
without that.

43:47.178 --> 43:49.887
[Jackie] And this fuckin' kid is
shitting in his fuckin' pants.

43:49.887 --> 43:52.261
We're driving to
a fuckin' bank robbery,

43:52.261 --> 43:54.053
and he's driving like
he works for the IRS.

43:54.053 --> 43:57.512
I had-- I had to reach over
and hit the fuckin' gas pedal

43:57.512 --> 44:00.095
-with my foot.
-[Keenan] Question is,

44:00.095 --> 44:01.970
why weren't you driving?

44:01.970 --> 44:04.261
Why is nobody asking
that question, Jack?

44:04.261 --> 44:06.178
Slander.

44:06.178 --> 44:08.136
I have never taken
a drink in my life.

44:08.136 --> 44:12.011
-I work for the FBI.
-[laughter]

44:12.011 --> 44:14.595
The kid ratted out
his own brother.

44:14.595 --> 44:18.345
Ryan, Jimmy Ryan.
Unbelievable.

44:18.345 --> 44:20.679
Well, like you once told me,

44:20.679 --> 44:22.261
things aren't what
they used to be.

44:23.637 --> 44:25.512
And you look like the hero.

44:26.595 --> 44:28.679
Some things never change.

44:29.762 --> 44:32.679
[Jackie]
Oh, fuck! Jesus.

44:32.679 --> 44:36.136
The fuckin'--
This motherfuckin' watch.

44:36.136 --> 44:39.679
I tell ya, Salvy, they never
give you enough credit.

44:39.679 --> 44:43.178
You were smart to get out.
Very smart.

44:43.178 --> 44:46.387
Jackie,
they forced  me out.

44:46.387 --> 44:48.929
Why do you think
I tried to warn ya?

44:48.929 --> 44:51.095
The whole "you're fuckin' up
your life" thing.

44:51.095 --> 44:52.887
They forced you out
for what?

44:53.929 --> 44:55.553
Informant went bad.

44:58.553 --> 45:01.929
-Oh, fuck me.
-Are you kidding me?

45:01.929 --> 45:03.053
[Jackie] Oh!

45:04.220 --> 45:05.720
This is the Tongs did that!

45:05.720 --> 45:06.845
[Clasby] In lipstick?

45:06.845 --> 45:08.303
Hang on, I got an idea.

45:09.470 --> 45:11.303
[phone beeps]

45:11.303 --> 45:14.970
[dialing]

45:14.970 --> 45:17.595
-[woman] Hello? Jackie?
-Hello.

45:17.595 --> 45:19.762
Hey, put your husband
on the phone.

45:19.762 --> 45:21.720
Put your fuckin'
husband on the phone!

45:21.720 --> 45:23.804
-All right, take it easy.
-[man] Yeah, what?

45:23.804 --> 45:26.470
Hey, it's Rohr.
Listen, I need a car.

45:26.470 --> 45:28.845
-Where are you?
-Down the Financial District.

45:28.845 --> 45:30.387
-What?
-Red sedan.

45:30.387 --> 45:32.095
Really?

45:32.095 --> 45:34.929
-Down by Washington.
-Oh. All right, all right.

45:34.929 --> 45:38.220
Hey, we're in luck.

45:38.220 --> 45:41.720
Did I tell you that
I got fuckin' mugged?

45:41.720 --> 45:44.929
I did.
Fuckin' couple three smokes,

45:44.929 --> 45:46.845
fuckin' two-by-four.

45:46.845 --> 45:48.470
But you know,
what really bothered me

45:48.470 --> 45:50.512
is how fuckin' dumb they were.

45:50.512 --> 45:53.887
There's a nice car,
illegally parked,

45:53.887 --> 45:55.762
situation just screamed cop,

45:55.762 --> 45:58.011
and they couldn't read
the fuckin' situation.

45:58.011 --> 46:00.679
I mean, even moolies
at least be smarter than that.

46:00.679 --> 46:04.095
It was just a better
class of criminal.

46:04.095 --> 46:07.220
What's gonna happen
when we got 'em all?

46:07.220 --> 46:08.970
Well, what do ya think
all this hollering

46:08.970 --> 46:11.053
about the Confidential
Informant Program is?

46:11.053 --> 46:14.470
They already got all
the illegitimate guys.

46:14.470 --> 46:17.470
All that's left now
is the half-legitimate guys.

46:17.470 --> 46:19.720
-Meaning us.
-Yep!

46:19.720 --> 46:21.345
Meaning us.

46:21.345 --> 46:23.053
Ta-da!

46:24.303 --> 46:26.303
[Clasby] Whose car is this?

46:26.303 --> 46:27.762
It's an informant's.

46:27.762 --> 46:29.470
What did I just tell you
happened to me?

46:29.470 --> 46:31.136
It happened to you,
it didn't happen to me.

46:31.136 --> 46:32.762
[scoffs]

46:37.345 --> 46:39.261
[keys jingle]

46:43.512 --> 46:45.762
Unlock the door.

46:45.762 --> 46:47.845
[lock clicks]

46:50.595 --> 46:51.720
[door slams]

46:51.720 --> 46:54.387
♪ dramatic music plays ♪

46:54.387 --> 46:55.845
[Jackie] Ohh.

46:55.845 --> 46:58.178
[engine turns over]

46:59.887 --> 47:01.845
What the fuck?!

47:04.220 --> 47:06.261
[coughs]

47:15.762 --> 47:18.679
-[Jackie laughs]
-[Clasby] Fucker!

47:18.679 --> 47:20.762
[laughing]

47:20.762 --> 47:22.595
Are you laughing?

47:24.178 --> 47:27.804
How do you fuck up a car bomb?

47:27.804 --> 47:30.595
-[laughs]
-You'll never learn.

47:30.595 --> 47:33.345
Oh, wait.
No, Salvy!

47:33.345 --> 47:35.428
But we got away!

47:35.428 --> 47:37.887
Sal, we got...
[laughs]

47:48.553 --> 47:50.762
So what would you
have me do with you?

47:50.762 --> 47:52.553
Depends on what you want.

47:52.553 --> 47:54.303
If you want me gone, I'm goin'.

47:54.303 --> 47:56.929
I have no argument
against my dismissal.

47:56.929 --> 47:58.553
Well, that's very
magnanimous of you.

47:58.553 --> 48:01.220
If you want me to stay,
your options widen.

48:03.220 --> 48:06.387
See, how we present
what happened

48:06.387 --> 48:08.011
is all a matter of perception.

48:08.011 --> 48:10.553
Kelly Kinicki was a case
the BPD couldn't solve.

48:10.553 --> 48:12.178
I ate shit on that.

48:12.178 --> 48:15.053
But Kinicki happened
before Charles Stuart.

48:15.053 --> 48:16.136
Stuart happened.

48:16.136 --> 48:18.095
Hiring practices changed.

48:18.095 --> 48:19.929
I'm hired.

48:19.929 --> 48:22.428
Then the new guy manages
to put away a Charlestown gang

48:22.428 --> 48:23.679
for three murders. Three.

48:23.679 --> 48:26.470
Ward, lay off the bullshit.

48:26.470 --> 48:28.595
Christ, you're not Jackie Rohr.

48:28.595 --> 48:31.303
You're not that good at it.
Not yet.

48:31.303 --> 48:34.220
No, we're not gonna
get rid of you that easy.

48:34.220 --> 48:35.929
We hired you for a reason.

48:39.136 --> 48:40.512
I appreciate that, Chief.

48:55.970 --> 48:58.428
[chatter]

49:03.804 --> 49:05.512
You know the last thing
I wanted to do

49:05.512 --> 49:07.970
when I took this job?

49:07.970 --> 49:09.762
Guns and drug cases,
I imagine.

49:09.762 --> 49:11.095
Is that what they're
giving you now?

49:11.095 --> 49:13.720
You think they'd miss
that opportunity?

49:13.720 --> 49:17.136
Yeah, we work a lot
of guns and drugs.

49:17.136 --> 49:20.762
We could do a lot of good
with a sympathetic prosecutor.

49:20.762 --> 49:22.303
I heard.

49:23.970 --> 49:25.470
Dee Ward,

49:25.470 --> 49:27.720
finally figured out
where you belong, huh?

49:27.720 --> 49:30.136
[Rachel] Hey.

49:30.136 --> 49:31.762
You still
feeling self-pity?

49:32.887 --> 49:35.845
-Maybe.
-Get over yourself.

49:42.095 --> 49:44.845
♪ dramatic music plays ♪

49:51.720 --> 49:53.929
I've been working
this file on Jackie.

49:53.929 --> 49:56.679
Now, what I have
is circumstantial,

49:56.679 --> 49:59.011
but it could be valuable to you.

49:59.011 --> 50:01.220
You know, if you still
have some people

50:01.220 --> 50:03.178
you wanna say "fuck you" to.

50:09.512 --> 50:13.428
[Jackie] And I look
at this killer, Donato Angiulo,

50:13.428 --> 50:16.553
-and I say to him--
-"Irony abounds."

50:18.679 --> 50:19.720
[Jackie] Why?

50:19.720 --> 50:21.220
Why didn't ya listen to me?

50:22.887 --> 50:24.553
Because the fact occurred
to me that every word

50:24.553 --> 50:27.220
out of your mouth since
we met was total bullshit.

50:27.220 --> 50:29.553
-I really thought ya understood.
-What, bullshit?

50:29.553 --> 50:31.637
That this whole town
is bullshit.

50:31.637 --> 50:33.428
I mean, look around ya.

50:33.428 --> 50:35.595
What do you think this place
we're sittin' right here

50:35.595 --> 50:37.720
is named after?

50:37.720 --> 50:40.011
-A book about Mayor Curley.
-Right.

50:40.011 --> 50:41.887
Spencer Tracy played him
in the movie.

50:41.887 --> 50:46.053
The lovable old mayor
who robbed this city blind.

50:46.053 --> 50:48.679
And what did Curley
name his own book?

50:48.679 --> 50:50.345
"I'd Do It Again!"

50:50.345 --> 50:52.970
Which in context means,
"I'd steal it all over again."

50:52.970 --> 50:55.762
How did he got away with it?

50:55.762 --> 50:57.804
He took care of people.

50:57.804 --> 51:00.261
You would've taken care of me?

51:00.261 --> 51:01.887
If you'd listened to me,
yeah.

51:01.887 --> 51:03.595
And here I was
this whole time,

51:03.595 --> 51:05.553
I thought you respected me.

51:05.553 --> 51:07.470
Ah, Dee.

51:07.470 --> 51:09.512
Don't make me feel bad.

51:10.804 --> 51:14.095
Do you feel bad?
Hmm?

51:14.095 --> 51:17.637
Would you do it again
if you had the chance?

51:17.637 --> 51:20.261
Probably, yeah,
I'd do it again.

51:21.679 --> 51:24.053
So, you're happy

51:24.053 --> 51:25.679
with how everything
turned out?

51:25.679 --> 51:26.970
You're happy?

51:26.970 --> 51:28.261
Yeah.

51:29.303 --> 51:30.929
Yeah, I'm happy.

51:33.720 --> 51:36.053
No...you're not.

51:37.261 --> 51:41.303
[indistinct chatter
in background]

51:41.303 --> 51:43.720
Didn't you ever wonder
what Jimmy Ryan told me

51:43.720 --> 51:45.136
to get him immunity?

51:49.470 --> 51:50.804
You're full of shit.

51:50.804 --> 51:52.595
Maybe.

51:52.595 --> 51:54.470
Maybe I'm waitin'.

51:57.845 --> 52:01.303
Dee, nobody listened
to King Kong

52:01.303 --> 52:05.178
after he made a thud
on the sidewalk.

52:05.178 --> 52:07.595
Yeah but I haven't
even begun to scale

52:07.595 --> 52:10.553
the building yet
and show this town my ass.

52:10.553 --> 52:12.470
But the day will come.

52:14.011 --> 52:16.637
And maybe I don't
come after you.

52:16.637 --> 52:18.470
Maybe you decide
to come after me.

52:20.345 --> 52:21.845
I'll be waitin'.

52:23.679 --> 52:25.804
Friend.

52:29.220 --> 52:32.804
["Ooh Child"
by The Five Stairsteps plays]

52:38.178 --> 52:39.178
♪ Hey ♪

52:42.845 --> 52:46.595
♪ Ooh child,
things are gonna get easier ♪

52:46.595 --> 52:50.637
-[minister] Change comes slow.
-[congregants affirming]

52:50.637 --> 52:54.178
-And often painfully...
-[woman] That's right.

52:54.178 --> 52:57.303
for those who would
seek change.

52:57.303 --> 53:01.887
But as we embark on
this journey together,

53:01.887 --> 53:06.053
all my friends and neighbors,

53:06.053 --> 53:08.637
I counsel you

53:08.637 --> 53:12.845
to seek comfort
where I have sought comfort.

53:12.845 --> 53:14.553
[congregants murmuring]

53:14.553 --> 53:17.804
You... are the salt
of the earth.

53:17.804 --> 53:19.804
[congregants affirming]

53:19.804 --> 53:21.929
The light of this world.

53:21.929 --> 53:23.261
[congregants affirming]

53:23.261 --> 53:26.345
A city on a hill
cannot be hidden.

53:27.804 --> 53:30.512
♪ Someday, someday, someday ♪

53:30.512 --> 53:33.261
